==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delegacy
<hw>Del`e*ga*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Delegate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
delegating, or state of being delegated; deputed power.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By way of <qex>delegacy</qex> or grand commission.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A body of delegates or commissioners; a
delegation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delegate</ent>⟦br⟧
